{{Infobox lake | name = Askjelldalsvatnet | image = | caption = | image_bathymetry = | caption_bathymetry = | location = [[Vaksdal]] ([[Hordaland]]) | coords = {{Coord|60|53|25|N|6|10|52|E|region:NO_type:waterbody_scale:200000|display=inline,title}} | type = | inflow = | outflow = | catchment = | basin_countries = Norway | length = | width = | area = {{convert|2.84|km2|abbr=on}} | depth = | max-depth = | volume = | residence_time = | shore = {{convert|10.49|km}} | elevation = {{convert|805|m}} | frozen = | islands = | cities = | reference = [[Norwegian Water Resources and Energy Directorate|NVE]] }}
'''Askjelldalsvatnet''' is a [[lake]] in the municipality of [[Vaksdal]] in [[Hordaland]] county, [[Norway]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yr.no/place/Norway/Hordaland/Vaksdal/Askjelldalsvatnet,_vetle/|title=Askjelldalsvatnet|publisher=[[yr.no]]|language=Norwegian|accessdate=2014-05-05}}</ref> The lake lies at an elevation of {{convert|805|m}} in the [[Vikafjell]] mountains between the valleys of [[Modalen]] and [[Eksingedalen]]. The {{convert|2.84|km2|adj=on}} lake has a [[dam]] at the southern end of the lake. The dam is used to regulate the water level so that the water can be used for [[hydro-electric]] power at a nearby power plant. The lake [[Skjerjavatnet]] lies about {{convert|1|km}} to the west.
