[[File:KP-1461.svg|thumb|KP-1461]]
'''Koronis Pharmaceuticals''' is a Seattle area biotechnology company founded in 1998. Koronis is dedicated to the development of [[Antiviral drug|antiviral]] therapeutics based on a novel mechanism, Viral Decay Acceleration (VDA). The Company’s lead product candidate is [[KP-1461]] for the treatment of [[HIV/AIDS|human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) infection]]. The company also has products in development for the treatment of [[hepatitis C]] and [[Human respiratory syncytial virus|RSV infection]].

