The '''Millan Committee''' was established in 1999 by the [[Scottish Parliament]] to review the law on mental health in Scotland. [[Bruce Millan]] was the chair of the committee. It reported in 2001.<ref>{{cite news|title=Call for mental health law repeal|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/scotland/1135627.stm|accessdate=26 May 2016|publisher=BBC News|date=25 January 2001}}</ref>

Its report was the basis of the [[Mental Health (Care and Treatment) (Scotland) Act 2003]].

